        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:49PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms 10 miles
south of Sheridan Lake, or 23 miles northeast of Lamar, moving north
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brandon, Sheridan Lake, Granada, and Bristol.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
